      "description": "Predicted force at 40 mm displacement within 5.1% of experimental mean; E/uval = 1.12. Strongest agreement across all three QoIs."
    }
  ],
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1) with documented QA procedures and regression test suite; FDA-internal build verification log available.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1 is a commercially validated FEA solver with ISO 9001-certified QA procedures. FDA internal build verification logs confirm the installed version matches the release checksum. Regression tests covering linear and nonlinear contact problems were executed and passed prior to analysis. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 suite (patch test, Hertz contact) reproduced within 1% of analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "Standard patch test and Hertz contact benchmark problems were executed in the analysis environment. Results agreed with analytical solutions to within 0.4% and 0.8% respectively, confirming correct code implementation. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change < 2% between medium and fine mesh; GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod assembly. Stiffness QoI changed by 1.3% between medium (1.2M elements) and fine (2.8M elements) meshes. Grid Convergence Index computed at 2.1%, well below the 5% threshold. Production mesh uses the medium density to balance accuracy and computational cost. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge to < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals monitored across all 120 load increments. Maximum residual norm at convergence was 4.7e-7. Energy balance error computed at 0.06% across the full load history. No divergence events observed. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by a second analyst; documented checklist of boundary condition and material assignment verification.",
      "rationale": "A second FDA analyst independently reviewed the model setup using a 47-item checklist covering geometry import, material assignments, contact definitions, boundary conditions, and load application. Two minor discrepancies in contact stiffness defaults were identified and corrected prior to final runs. Final model sign-off documented. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with frictional contact is appropriate for the screw-rod construct; sensitivity study on friction coefficient.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw construct operates in the elastic-to-early-plastic regime under F1717 loading. A bilinear isotropic hardening model with Ti-6Al-4V parameters (E=114 GPa, σy=880 MPa, Et=2.3 GPa) is well-established for this alloy. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) between screw and rod was validated against published tribological data. Sensitivity analysis varying μ from 0.15 to 0.30 showed < 3% change in stiffness QoI. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (elastic modulus, yield strength, hardening modulus) were obtained from tensile coupon testing of the same production lot as the test constructs (n=5 coupons per lot). Geometric dimensions of each test article were measured by CMM prior to assembly. Nominal CAD geometry was updated with mean measured dimensions. Uncertainty in material properties propagated through the model; contribution to total uncertainty budget < 2%. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lot; traceability to manufacturing records; dimensional inspection of all samples.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-lot components with full traceability to manufacturing batch records. CMM dimensional inspection confirmed all components within drawing tolerances. Constructs distributed across two independent laboratories (n=6 Lab A, n=5 Lab B) to assess inter-laboratory variability. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness was 3.1%, indicating acceptable reproducibility. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two distinct load levels or configurations tested to assess model predictive range; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) recorded and within ASTM F1717 tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single load configuration (axial compression-bending per ASTM F1717 Section 8.3) at ambient laboratory conditions. Environmental conditions were recorded and confirmed within ASTM tolerances. However, only one test configuration was employed; no secondary load level or alternative fixture geometry was included to probe the model's predictive range beyond the primary QoIs. This limits confidence in model generalizability. Achieved level 2 falls below the required level 3 for this model risk level.",
      "gap": "Single test condition only; required level 3 not met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented mapping of experimental boundary conditions to FEA constraints; fixture compliance characterized and incorporated.",
      "rationale": "Test machine fixture compliance was characterized by a separate compliance calibration run and incorporated as a spring boundary condition in the FEA model. The load application point and support geometry were replicated from ASTM F1717 fixture drawings confirmed against laboratory photographs. Torque applied to set screws was measured with a calibrated torque wrench and translated to a pre-stress condition in the model. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Three primary QoIs compared: construct stiffness (E/uval=1.41, 6.2% difference), yield force (E/uval=1.78, 8.7% difference), and force at 40 mm displacement (E/uval=1.12, 5.1% difference). All three metrics satisfy both the E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% acceptance criteria. Comparison plots with experimental scatter bands provided in Appendix C. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory submission claims and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness is the primary performance metric in the regulatory submission. Yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are secondary metrics tied to fatigue life prediction and clinical failure (implant bending/fracture leading to revision surgery). All three QoIs appear explicitly in the 510(k) performance testing section. The mapping from QoI to clinical risk was reviewed by the clinical affairs team. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) is the same scenario as the COU; no extrapolation beyond validated domain required.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is identical in scope to the COU: static compression-bending of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct per ASTM F1717. No extrapolation to different loading modes, screw diameters, or patient populations is required. The model is applied within its validated domain. Relevance is direct and complete. Required level 3 achieved."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions achieving level 2 against a required level 3 — was reviewed by the assessment team. The shortfall is mitigated by the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (maximum E/uval = 1.78, well within the 1.96 bound), the use of two independent laboratories, and the direct correspondence between the validation scenario and the COU. The team determined that the weight of evidence supports a Medium assurance declaration and an Accepted decision for regulatory submission purposes. No additional testing is required at this stage.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
